Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is excited to offer for sale a prime corner site for sale in Smithfield by way of public auction.

This is a fantastic opportunity to acquire a freehold site with prominent exposure to The Horsley Drive.

+ Opportunity to occupy or develop
+ Corner Site with dual street access - great for developers seeking to maximise site coverage
+ Site Area 8,053 sqm (approx.).
+ Ability to utilise existing improvements for owner occupiers
+ 81 metre frontage on The Horsley Drive and 99.8 metre frontage on O'Connell Street
+ Side street access via O'Connell Street, providing for a rear storage yard
+ Zoned: IN1 General Industrial
+ Opportunity to own your own piece of this tightly held and well established industrial hub of Smithfield

For Sale via On-Site Auction on Wednesday 31st August, 2016 at 10:30am.

For a full information pack or to arrange an inspection please contact either of the exclusive agents Elijah or Peter.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Extremely Rare Land Opportunity On The Horsley Drive - Auction

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The site is near the intersection of the Cumberland Highway
and The Horsley Drive Smithfield. Upon this intersection are
both a prominent Shell Express (operating 24/7), Coles
Supermarket and Smithfield Tavern. The site enjoys dual
access from both the Cumberland Highway and The Horsley
Drive. The site is level, mainly clear of obstruction excluding
an abandoned building facing the Horsley Drive.

- Site Profile

A combination of two allotments – Lot 1 & Lot 2 in DP 207618.

• Lot 1 - Vacant land
  56 Smithfield Road, Smithfield
  Site area 740sqm (approximately) subject to survey
  Clear of any structure
  Access off The Cumberland Highway

• Lot 2 - former 'Smithfield Post Office'
  678 The Horsley Drive, Smithfield
  Site area 873sqm (approximately) subject to survey
  Building structure destroyed by fire
  Access off The Horsey Drive

• Zoning - B2 Local Centre (both lots)

CBRE is pleased to present an opportunity to secure a freestanding office and warehouse facility in the tightly held Smithfield Industrial precinct.

- Total Undercover Areas | Warehouse: 790sqm*, Office: 71sqm*, Awning: 360sqm*.
- Access via two (2) roller shutter doors
- Internal clearances up to 5.5m (approx).
- Ample concrete hardstand enabling excellent container loading/unloading.
- Recently refurbished multi-levelled office accommodation carpeted and air conditioned.
- Will be sold vacant and ready to occupy
- Zoned IN1 General Industrial
- Close proximity to main arterial roads such as The Cumberland Highway, Great Western Highway & The M4 Western Motorway

The property will be sold by way of public auction on-site: WEDNESDAY, 10 JUNE 2020 AT 2PM (AEST)

For a copy of the information memorandum or to arrange an inspection, please contact the exclusively listed agents.

*All areas are approximated.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: AUCTION | FREESTANDING INDUSTRIAL FACILITY + SECURE CONCRETE YARD

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
On behalf of GM Property Group, Colliers International in conjunction with CBRE, have the pleasure in offering the opportunity to acquire a land-mark industrial estate, offering multiple value add opportunities through development in the future. Underpinned by its sheer scale, strong tenancy profile, long WALE, and  substantial infill land holding, we expect this asset will attract strong interest from the market.

•	WALE – 5.6 years by income 
•	100% fully leased
•	$2,609,311pa* net passing income 
•	24,100sqm* building area
•	Site area – 5.52 hectares*
•	DA approval on 6,000sqm pad
•	Excellent access to M4 Motorway
•	5.5 star NABERS Energy rating
 
For sale via an International Offers to Purchase campaign, closing: Friday, 8th June 2018 at 4pm (AEST).



*approximate
